BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:SvhpnS3JsQUouOB1E2FEG
SUMMARY:Virtual AI Practitioner Part 2: Introduction to Generative AI
DTSTAMP:20260214T003619Z
DTSTART:20260216T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, February 16\, 2026\, 1 - 4pm\n\nIn this AI foundationa
	l 6-part series\, you will learn fundamental concepts and terminology rela
	ted to artificial intelligence\, machine learning\, deep learning\, and ge
	nerative AI.\n\nLocation Link: Online\n\nRoom Location: Level 4 - Room 3\n
	\nRegistration Required: Registration is required.\n\nDetailed Description
	: Explore the relationships between these different AI approaches and unde
	rstand how to distinguish scenarios suited for traditional software method
	s versus AI/ML techniques.\, This session introduces you to the fundamenta
	l concepts\, capabilities\, principles\, use cases\, and AWS services rela
	ted to generative AI. You will learn how to identify potential use cases f
	or generative AI\, understand its advantages compared to other solutions\,
	 recognize key risks\, and learn the basic elements of prompt engineering 
	to effectively interact with AI models.\, This session covers AWS generati
	ve AI services including Amazon SageMaker AI\, Amazon Bedrock\, and Amazon
	 Q\, teaching you when and how to use each service appropriately. Through 
	hands-on activities using PartyRock \\(an Amazon Bedrock playground\\)\, y
	ou will gain practical experience structuring prompts and working with lar
	ge language models. The session aligns with concepts covered in the AWS Ce
	rtified AI Practitioner exam but is designed as an introductory overview r
	ather than exam preparation.\,\n\nIn this session\, you will learn to:\n\n
	Identify potential use cases for generative AI\, Describe the advantages o
	f generative AI as compared to other types of solutions\, Summarize the ke
	y risks introduced with generative AI\, Define the fundamental elements of
	 a prompt\, This session is intended for one or more of the following: Ind
	ividuals who are ready to learn about AWS Cloud technologies\, Individuals
	 in both technical and non-technical roles\, Individuals looking reskill f
	or the AWS Cloud\, Business decision makers\, It is recommended that you h
	ave the following general skills: Understanding of artificial intelligence
	\, Understanding of AWS global infrastructure\, Understanding of AWS netwo
	rking services and how to build a functioning Amazon VPC solution.\, Under
	standing of Amazon S3\, Amazon EBS\, and Amazon EFS\, Understanding of AWS
	 security services\, Understanding of virtual computer services using Amaz
	on E2\, These skills can be gained by taking the following AWS Skills Cent
	er session: AWS Skills Centers: Becoming a Cloud Practitioner - Parts 1-4\
	, AWS Skills Centers: Becoming an AI Practitioner - Part 1\, Thanks to our
	 partner\n\nAWS Skills Center Seattle .\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration r
	equired. Register\n\nhere . Link to virtual event will be sent after regis
	tration.\, The program aligns with concepts covered in the AWS Certified A
	I Practitioner exam but is designed as an introductory overview rather tha
	n exam preparation. The classes are led by AWS Certified Instructors and i
	n partnership with the\n\nAWS Skills Centers .\n\nContact Us: If you have 
	questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Acc
	ommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilities at
	 Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the e
	vent to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open t
	o the public.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/virtual-ai-practitioner-p
	art-2-introduction-to-generative-ai/18084340/2026-02-16T00
LOCATION:MAKERS\, 92 Lenora Street\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
