	 kids ages 0-2 and their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun lear
	ning activities.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nColumbia Branch\n\nRoom Location: Me
	eting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDeta
	iled Description: Early Learning is a great way for babies and their famil
	ies to develop learning\, literacy\, and language skills as well as commun
	ity with other families.\, We read stories\, sing songs\, and have engagin
	g\, educational activities that help kids and their caregivers grow togeth
	er.\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration is not required but these programs ar
	e very popular and the room capacity can fill up quickly.\, Tickets are av
	ailable from staff 15 minutes before story time begins.\, \, Families of a
	ll ages are welcome\, though this early learning program is intended for k
	ids ages 0-15 months old\, their caregivers and families.\n\nContact Us: I
	f you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.
	\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disa
	bilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days b
	efore the event to request accommodations.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
