UID:L9i2g3WmJbP7I0USrjMPI
SUMMARY:Reduced and Free Transit Fare Enrollment
DTSTAMP:20260214T003620Z
DTSTART:20260217T213000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, February 17\, 2026\, 1:30 - 3:30pm\n\nLow-income indi
	viduals and individuals with disabilities can receive a reduced-fare ORCA 
	LIFT transit pass.\n\nIndividuals receiving TANF\, RCA\, PWA\, SSI\, HEN\,
	 or ABD can receive a subsidized year-long pass.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nNort
	hgate Branch\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDe
	tailed Description:\n\n\,\n\nCatholic Community Services\n\nwill be onsite
	 to register interested individuals with disabilities or with household in
	come below 200% of the federal poverty level for reduced-cost or free ORCA
	 Lift card.\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\nPlease bring:\n\nPhoto ID\, Your Provid
	erOne number OR DSHS Client ID number\, Most recent copy of your DSHS awar
	d letter \\(Your TANF award letter or HEN award letter will work.\\)\n\nCo
	ntact Us: To contact\n\nCatholic Community Services \, call\n\n206-960-158
	2\n\nor\n\n206-867-0710.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodati
	ons for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\
	n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All L
	ibrary programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All 
	Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/reduced-and-free-transit-
	fare-enrollment/17738974/2026-02-17T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:elP8zgwrTnTWdP6HM0Dpt
SUMMARY:Online Job Applications
DTSTAMP:20260214T003620Z
DTSTART:20260217T213000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, February 17\, 2026\, 1:30 - 3pm\n\nDiscover how to ef
	fectively search for jobs\, complete online applications\, and ensure your
	 submissions stand out.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Locat
	ion: Level 4 - Room 2\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not requir
	ed.\n\nDetailed Description: Navigate the world of online job applications
	 with confidence in this presentation led by Employment Specialist\n\nCore
	y Minatani\n\nfrom Evergreen Goodwill&'s Job Training and Education Center
	 \\(JTEC\\). Corey will guide you through common challenges\, including cr
	eating accounts\, uploading resumes\, and responding to application questi
	ons.\, This session is perfect for anyone looking to build their digital j
	ob-seeking skills and streamline the application process. Get the tools an
	d knowledge you need to land your next opportunity!\, Thanks to our partne
	r\n\nEvergreen Goodwill Job Training & Education.\n\nEvent Logistics: Ther
	e will be time after the presentation to ask questions.\, Find out more ab
	out our\n\nEmployment Workshops .\n\nContact Us: If you have questions abo
	ut this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: 
	We can provide accommodations for people with disabilities at Library even
	ts. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to reque
	st accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.
	\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/online-job-applications/1
	8084341/2026-02-17T00
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Fk2vS5nQ0sJzj_TFEOXnd
SUMMARY:English Conversation Circle
DTSTAMP:20260214T003620Z
DTSTART:20260217T213000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, February 17\, 2026\, 1 - 2:30pm\n\nPractice your Engl
	ish Conversation skills with other adult learners.\n\nPractique su inglés.
	\n\nLuyện tập tiếng Anh của quý vị.\n\n练习英语。\n\n練習英語。\n\n英会話の練習をしましょう。\n\n
	Ku Celceli Ingiriisigaaga.\n\nእንግሊዘኛዎንይለማመዱ።\n\nእንግሊዘኛኹምተለማመዱ።\n\nAfaan In
	gilizii kee shaakali.\n\nمارس لغتك الإنجليزية\n\n.دینک نیرمت ار دوخ یسیلگن
	ا\n\n.ئړک نیرمت يسیلګنا هلپخ\n\nПрактикуйте вашу англійську.\n\nПрактикуйт
	есь в английском языке.\n\nPratiquez votre anglais.\n\nPractique seu inglê
	s.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 4 - Room 1
	\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Descr
	iption: Discuss relevant topics in small groups to gain self-confidence an
	d improve your speaking and listening.\, This class is for adult\, beginne
	r-level English language learners \\(levels 2-6\\) only.\,\n\nThe current 
	series runs Tuesday\, January 6 and ends on Tuesday\, March 10.\, Thanks t
	o our partner\n\nLiteracy Source .\,\n\n----------------------------------
	-------------------------------\, Practique su inglés. Debata temas releva
	ntes en grupos pequeños para ganar confianza en sí mismo y mejorar su habl
	a y comprensión auditiva. Esta clase está dirigida a estudiantes adultos d
	e inglés de nivel 2 en adelante \\(principiante/intermedio\\).\,\n\nLas cl
	ases actuales comienzan el martes 6 de enero y finalizan el martes 10 de m
	arzo.\,\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------
	--\, Luyện tập tiếng Anh của quý vị. Thảo luận các chủ đề liên quan trong 
	các nhóm nhỏ để có được sự tự tin và cải thiện khả năng nói và nghe của qu
	ý vị. Lớp học này dành cho người học tiếng Anh người lớn từ cấp 2 trở lên 
	\\(sơ cấp/trung cấp\\).\,\n\nCác lớp học hiện tại diễn ra vào thứ Ba\, ngà
	y 6 tháng 1 và kết thúc vào thứ Ba\, ngày 10 tháng 3.\,\n\n---------------
	--------------------------------------------------\, 练习英语。 以小组形式讨论相关话题，增强自
