BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wumq8i070TG8vOxzz2_eC
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260219T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community 
	& Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-02-19T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nFxQXDSRykF8Mm2aRM9n1
SUMMARY:Melodies of the Diaspora: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Mo
	nth
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260219T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Black History Month 2026\, the City of Bellev
	ue is working with community partners to present "Melodies of the Diaspora
	: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Month\," an art exhibition featur
	ing the work of Pacific Northwest Black artists on display at the Bellevue
	 Arts Museum and Bellevue City Hall and is designed to take visitors on a 
	chronological journey of Black art through downtown Bellevue.\n\nThe exhib
	ition will feature paintings\, photography\, sculptures\, textiles and fas
	hion and is curated by Jay Taylor\, Fancy Vargas and Jerry Lee.\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/melodies-of-the-diaspora-
	celebrating-100-years-of-black-history-month/18022797/2026-02-19T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Arts Museum\, 510 Belllevue Way NE\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
