BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1SPPwABe2EG0vUqb9AOji
SUMMARY:Homebuyer Education Workshop [VIRTUAL]
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260221T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:This is a free five-hour workshop to help you meet the WA State
	 Housing Finance Commission’s education requirements for down payment assi
	stance and a variety of affordable housing programs and opportunities for 
	qualified applicants! These requirements include the successful completion
	 of a Homebuyers Education Seminar meeting the current FHA\, Fannie Mae\, 
	FreddieMac\, and SMBA benchmark standards.  \n\nAt the conclusion of the w
	orkshop\, participants will receive a certificate of achievement from the 
	WA State Housing Finance Commission and DFI valid for two years from the d
	ate of issuance.  \n\nTo join our next workshop\, please complete and subm
	it the following registration form at least 24-hours before your selected 
	workshop date. Once this form has been submitted\, be sure to check your e
	mail for a digital confirmation\, as well as additional follow up and impo
	rtant information from a ULMS Housing Department staff member.   \n\nVirtu
	al workshops are held every 3rd and 4th Saturday of the month from 10:00AM
	 – 3:30PM. A Zoom link will be sent to you via a ULMS Housing department s
	taff member upon completing registration.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/homebuyer-education-works
	hop-virtual/17157120/2026-02-21T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OL3p6vhsux21vp3NkQVSH
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Clarke Beach Park
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260221T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Clarke Beach Park Work Party\n\nHelp us remove weeds and spre a
	d mulch in Clarke Beach Park. Weeds make it harder for native plants to g 
	row by overcrowding them and outcompeting them for resources. We want to p
	 rotect the native plants that are in the park! Once we remove the weeds\,
	 we'll spread a layer of mulch to cover the bare ground. Mulch is an incre
	d ible resource for degraded environments. It helps with weed suppression\
	, water retention\, and to create healthier soil.\n\nAll ages welcome\, no
	 experience required. Gloves\, tools\, and small snacks provided. \n\nPlea
	se note: we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer with a p a
	rent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Saturday\, Febr
	uary 21st\, 10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Clarke Beach Park \n\nWhat to bring: Dress 
	for the weather in clothes you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: long pan
	ts\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring water. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools 
	will be provided.\n\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup.org/7CADJ\n\nFr
	om SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-clarke-
	beach-park/18066404/2026-02-21T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
