BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:h4b7BlS2iKjNE6plLpJrm
SUMMARY:Woven Willow Plant Support
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260221T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Erin Cox. Learn traditional garden weaving made from 
	locally grown willow – no metal\, no plastic and 100% biodegradable. Histo
	rically\, farmers and gardeners would have tended a willow or hazel coppic
	e to harvest from each winter that provided a plethora of long flexible wh
	ips for weaving. This is your chance to take a step back in time and weave
	 a little piece of history while you make a beautiful and functional plant
	 support. All materials provided. $84 BBGS Member/$120 Non-Member\n\nFrom 
	SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/woven-willow-plant-suppor
	t/17923218/2026-02-21T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
