BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bLwp946w9-htO4px_gwep
SUMMARY:Northwest Flower & Garden Festival
DTSTAMP:20260214T003621Z
DTSTART:20260222T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:The 37th annual Northwest Flower & Garden Festival\, presented 
	by the Puyallup Tribe of Indians\, returns to the Seattle Convention Cente
	r this February 18-22 for another unforgettable celebration of horticultur
	e\, design\, and community. This year’s theme\, Spring Parade\, invites vi
	sitors to celebrate the beauty of renewal\, creativity\, and cultural conn
	ection through lush displays\, expert seminars\, and immersive experiences
	!\n\nStep into Spring with more than 600 vendor booths featuring garden to
	ols\, home decor\, jewelry\, and high-end art\, plus a Plant Market with o
	ver 60 nurseries selling houseplants\, perennials\, and native species. Yo
	u can’t leave without exploring over 20 dazzling display gardens or attend
	ing seminars and workshops hosted by home and garden experts.\\* Whether y
	ou're a seasoned gardener seeking inspiration or simply looking to embrace
	 the promise of spring\, the Northwest Flower & Garden Festival offers fiv
	e days of discovery and connection that will leave you eager to dig into t
	he season ahead!\n\nLearn more about the festival and purchase early bird 
	tickets at www.gardenshow.com. \n\n\\*Please note that some special events
	 require additional tickets\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/northwest-flower-garden-f
	estival/17987282/2026-02-22T00
LOCATION:Seattle Convention Center\, 705 Pike St\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT9H
END:VEVENT
